%N A396180 Consider the square spiral with its cells numbered starting at 0, as in A308884 and A274641. Three players, X, Y, and Z, play in rotation, beginning with X. When it is a player's turn, he places a queen at the smallest unoccupied cell not attacked by an existing queen belonging to a different player. Sequence lists squares occupied by an X queen.
%C A396180 This sequence together with A396181-A396183 partition the nonnegative integers.
